<h2>
Literature and Texts in the Ojibwe Language
</h2>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"><b><A HREF="
http://cal.bemidjistate.edu/english/donovan/Two_Women.html
">Two Women</a>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Ojibwe story with hypertext for language learners.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"><b><A HREF="
http://legends.knet.on.ca/
">Saga of Iyash</a>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Traditional legend in Oji-Cree and English, written in syllabics and recorded in RealAudio.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"><b><A HREF="
http://www.bigorrin.org/archive88.htm
">Naming as Cultural Transmission</a>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Story of a naming ceremony told in Ojibwe with English translation.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"><b><A HREF="
http://www.mchigeeng.net/kinoomaadoog/
">Kinoomaadoog</a>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Research project of the MChigeeng Nishnaabek includes speeches, interviews with elders, and other Ojibwe transcripts.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"><b><A HREF="
http://www.native-languages.org/jiisas.htm
">Christmas Story in Anishinaabemowin</a>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Text from an 1884 translation of the New Testament into the Ojibwe language.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"><b><A HREF="
http://www.archive.org/details/rosettaproject_otw_ortho-1
">Ottawa Orthography</a></b> <IMG SRC="star.gif" ALT="*"> <b><A HREF="
http://www.archive.org/details/rosettaproject_otw_morsyn-1
">Ottawa Grammar</a></b> <IMG SRC="star.gif" ALT="*"> <b><A HREF="
http://www.archive.org/details/rosettaproject_otw_gen-1
">Ottawa Bible Translation</a></b>  <IMG SRC="star.gif" ALT="*"> <b><A HREF="
http://www.archive.org/details/rosettaproject_otw_vertxt-2
">Ottawa Text</a></b>  <IMG SRC="star.gif" ALT="*"> <b><A HREF="
http://www.archive.org/details/rosettaproject_otw_vertxt-1
">Ottawa Story</a>:</b> <br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Scanned-in Ottawa language materials from the Rosetta Project.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"><b><A HREF="
http://www.archive.org/details/rosettaproject_ojs_detail-1
">Severn Ojibwe Language</a></b> <IMG SRC="star.gif" ALT="*"> <b><A HREF="
http://www.archive.org/details/rosettaproject_ojs_ortho-1
">Severn Ojibwa Orthography</a></b> <IMG SRC="star.gif" ALT="*"> <b><A HREF="
http://www.archive.org/details/rosettaproject_ojs_gen-1
">Oji-Cree Bible Stories</a></b>  <IMG SRC="star.gif" ALT="*"> <b><A HREF="
http://www.archive.org/details/rosettaproject_ojs_ortho-2
">Severn Ojibwa Alphabet</a>:</b> <br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Severn Ojibwe language materials from the Rosetta Project.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"><b><A HREF="
https://web.archive.org/web/20000612083158/http://christusrex.org/www1/pater/JPN-ojibwa.html
">Lord's Prayer: Ojibwa</a></b> <IMG SRC="star.gif" ALT="*"> <b><A HREF="
https://web.archive.org/web/20000612083158/http://christusrex.org/www1/pater/JPN-ojibwa-eastern.html
">Lord's Prayer: Ottawa</a></b> <IMG SRC="star.gif" ALT="*"> <b><A HREF="
https://web.archive.org/web/20000612083158/http://christusrex.org/www1/pater/JPN-ojibwa-northern.html
">Lord's Prayer: Severn Ojibwa (Oji-Cree)</a>:</b> <br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Christian prayers translated into the Ojibwa language.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"><b><A HREF="
http://www.biblescanada.com/catalog/1567.htm
">Northern Ojibwe Bible</a>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Old and New Testament translations into the Sault<img src="singledot.png">eaux Ojibwe language, in print and on audiocassette.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"><b><A HREF="
http://www.language-museum.com/encyclopedia/o/ojibwa-eastern.php
">Eastern Ojibwa Genesis</a></b> <IMG SRC="star.gif" ALT="*"> <b><A HREF="
http://www.language-museum.com/encyclopedia/o/ojibwa-northern.php
">Northern Ojibwa Genesis</a>:</b> <br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Bible passages in the Ojibwe language.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"><b><A HREF="
http://www.language-museum.com/encyclopedia/o/ojibwa.php
">Language Museum: Ojibwa</a>:</b> <br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Ojibwe language sample.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"><b><A HREF="
http://www.ohchr.org/EN/UDHR/Pages/Language.aspx?LangID=ojb
">Human Rights: Ojibway</a>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Translation of the Universal Declaration of Human Rights into the Ojibwe language.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"><b><A HREF="
http://www.cthr-mcdp.com/plaques/OjiCree.html
">Canadian Human Rights Tribute: Oji-Cree</a></b> <IMG SRC="star.gif" ALT="*"> <b><A HREF="
http://www.cthr-mcdp.com/plaques/OjibwaWestBay.html
">Canadian Human Rights: West Bay Ojibwa</a>:</b> <br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Plaques in the Ojibwa Indian language.
<BR>

