<H2>
Ojibwe Proper Names
</H2>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"><b><A HREF="
http://nativenet.uthscsa.edu/archive/nc/9511/0300.html
">Acquiring a Native American Name</a>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Expla<img src="singledot.png">nation of Ojibwe naming traditions by an Ojibwe mother.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"><b><A HREF="
http://www.maquah.net/Names/index.html
">Historical Ojibwe Names</a>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
A database of Chippewa Indian names from the 1800's.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"><b><A HREF="
http://cal.bemidjistate.edu/english/donovan/placenames.html
">Ojibwe Place Names</a></b> <IMG SRC="star.gif" ALT="*"> <b><A HREF="
https://web.archive.org/web/20091027141347/http://www.geocities.com/Athens/9479/ojibwe.html
">Ojibwe Placenames</a>:</b> 
<br> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Ojibwe-language place names and their meanings.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"><b><A HREF="
https://www.historymuseum.ca/cmc/exhibitions/aborig/fp/fpz2d06e.shtml
">Aboriginal Place Names of Ontario</a>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Map of Ontario labeled with traditional Huron and Ojibwa names with their meanings.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"><b><A HREF="
http://www.native-languages.org/names.htm
">American Indian Pet Names</a>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Our new fundraiser offering names for dogs and other animals in Native American languages (including Ojibway).
